<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11124e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11124e">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11124e"> 124(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> is the sun up (arrest)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Arrestation de Chateaubriand</b> Le 20 juin, &agrave; quatre heures du matin, Baptiste, &agrave; mon service depuis longtemps, entre dans ma chambre, s&apos;approche de mon lit et me dit: &ldquo;Monsieur, la cour est pleine d&apos;hommes qui se sont plac&eacute;s &agrave; toutes les portes, apr&egrave;s avoir force&eacute; Desbrosses &agrave; ouvrir la porte cohc&egrave;re, et voil&agrave; trois <i>messieurs</i> qui veulent vous parler.&rdquo; Comme il achevait ses mots, les <i>messieurs</i> entrent, et le chef, s&apos;approchant tr&egrave;s poliment de mon lit, me d&eacute;clare qu&apos;il a ordre de m&apos;arr&acirc;ter et de me mener &agrave; la pr&eacute;fecture de police. Je lui demandai si le soleil &eacute;tait lev&eacute;, ce qui exigeait la loi, et s&apos;il &eacute;tait porteur d&apos;un ordre l&eacute;gal: &hellip; <br><font color="green">[Chateaubriand Under Arrest: June 20, at four in the morning, Baptist, long in my service, enters my room, approaches my bed and says to me: &ldquo;Sir, the courtyard is full of men positioned at all doors, having forced Desbrosses to open the main entrance, here are three gentlemen who want to speak to you.&rdquo; As he finished his words, the gentlemen enter, and the chief, very politely approaching my bed, tells me that he has an order to arrest me and take me to the prefecture of police. <mark>I asked him if the sun had risen</mark>, as required by law, and if he was the bearer of a legal order]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 163</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
